Zambia’s President Sata Increases Retirement Age to 65 From 55

-- B y   A n t h o n y   M u k w i t a
-- 
2011-10-04T08:20:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/zambia-s-president-sata-increases-retirement-age-to-65-from-55.html
Zambia’s new president,  Michael Sata ,
said he’s instructed the cabinet secretary to increase the
country’s retirement age to 65 years from 55 years.  Sata commented in Lusaka today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anthony Mukwita at 
